Gemma-4 GEGLU + FP4 NaN-clamp patch for container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly.

Adds one patch-application step for an upstream PR not yet merged:
  - PR #22928: GEGLU activation + FP4 block scale NaN clamp (SM120/121)

PR #22929 (per-expert NVFP4 weight loading) was DROPPED 2026-06-19: it has
landed upstream, so re-applying it duplicated a now-dead mapping block and its
second hunk no longer matched the refactored load_weights loop.

The patch targets the sglang Python source tree (python/sglang/srt/) and is
applied AFTER the SM121 sgl-kernel patch but BEFORE `uv pip install ./python`
so the installed package picks up the changes.

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly AFTER
dockerfile-sm121.patch has been applied.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -278,6 +278,20 @@
         echo "=== Skipping sgl-kernel-sm121-debug.patch (APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG=${APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_SM121_DEBUG}) ==="; \
     fi
 
+# Gemma-4 GEGLU + FP4 NaN-clamp patch (PR #22928, not yet upstream).
+# PR #22929 (per-expert NVFP4 weight loading) was DROPPED 2026-06-19 — it landed
+# upstream (sglang main builds per_expert_params_mapping via
+# FusedMoE.make_expert_params_mapping() and load_weights handles the
+# nvidia/Gemma-4-*-NVFP4 per-expert layout natively).
+# Applied to the sglang Python source before pip install so the installed
+# dist-packages picks up the changes.
+COPY patches/sglang-gemma4-geglu-nan-clamp.patch /tmp/sglang-gemma4-geglu-nan-clamp.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang && \
+    echo "=== Applying sglang-gemma4-geglu-nan-clamp.patch (PR #22928) ===" && \
+    patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sglang-gemma4-geglu-nan-clamp.patch && \
+    patch -p1 < /tmp/sglang-gemma4-geglu-nan-clamp.patch && \
+    echo 'Gemma-4 NVFP4 patch applied successfully'
+
 # Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch).
 # Moved here from its original early-stage location so the installed
 # dist-packages picks up the patched nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh above.
